# Documentation Standards

## Language and Tone

- A: professional, precise, approachable
- A: active voice; concise
- N: subjective descriptors - use measurable terms

## Content Quality

- A: honest, direct, factual; acknowledge limits
- N: marketing/superlatives/buzzwords
- A: technically accurate; verify claims; precise terms
- A: audience-appropriate depth
- A: document what exists (not future plans)
- A: descriptive link text (N: "click here", "see this")
- A: human-centered where relevant; concrete examples

## Structure

- Start with overview and purpose
- Middle: implementation details and usage
- End: examples and troubleshooting
- A: logical flow, consistent terms

## Accessibility

- A: include alt text for images (WCAG requirement)

## Consistency

- A: consistent capitalization and punctuation across list items
- A: consistent list formatting within same list
